    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to style and layout web pages. It controls colors, fonts, spacing, positioning, and responsiveness."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why Use CSS?"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Improve UI design and layout**",
        "**Separate content (HTML) from styling (CSS)**",
        "**Reuse styles across multiple pages**",
        "**Make websites responsive and modern**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Types of CSS"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Type", "Description"],
        "rows": [
          ["Inline CSS", "Applied directly inside HTML elements"],
          ["Internal CSS", "Defined inside <style> tag in <head>"],
          ["External CSS", "Stored in separate .css file"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Inline CSS Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<p style=\"color: blue;\">Hello CSS</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Internal CSS Example"
    },
